cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.CR, cs.IT

The paper discusses the deployment of Virtual Network Functions (VNFs) in network operator environments to facilitate dynamic service chaining. This topic falls under the area of network infrastructure (cs.NI) and data centers (cs.DC). The paper also presents a model for minimizing network-resource consumption, which falls under the area of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the network-resource consumption of various service-chaining strategies, which falls under the area of cryptography and security (cs.CR) and information theory (cs.IT).
